26/05/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Police have arrested a British expert in connection with a landmine explosion that left two dead and ten seriously injured. Graham Rees, 45, is chief of the UK-registered Handicap International charity. Two of its employees were conducting a mine-clearing class Monday when the blast occurred. A police spokeswoman said that Rees and Emin Durakovic, an expert from Bosnia and Herzegovina, would be held accountable for the use of live ammunition during the exercise.
In other news, Albanian President Alfred Moisiu met with visiting Kosovo Trade and Industry Minister Ali Jakupi on Tuesday. They discussed bilateral economic ties and ways to enhance them, including construction of the Durres-Kukes-Pristina highway. (The Independent, BBC, ATA, BBC, Scotsman - 25/05/04)
